Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the application of a natural language chatbot system in language learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the chatbot system uses pattern-matching mechanisms to generate responses. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the chatbot system may use machine learning techniques to improve its responses. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the study involves the interaction between humans and the chatbot system. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper may touch on the societal implications of using chatbot systems in language learning.
